# Purpose

Enforce MongoDB repository patterns, document schema validation on read, and transaction usage.

# Rules

## Repository Pattern

- All MongoDB operations MUST go through repository classes in `aop/db/mongo/repository/`.
- Current repositories: `UserRepository`, `JobsRepository`.
- Repositories are instantiated with a `Db` instance. Collection name comes from `config.db.collection.<name>.name`.
- DO NOT call `db.collection()` outside of a repository class.

## Schema Validation on Read

Every document returned from MongoDB MUST be validated against a Zod schema before use:

```typescript
const doc = await this.db.collection(this.collectionName).findOne({ email });

if (!doc) return null;

const result = parseSchema(userDocumentSchema, doc);

if (!result.success) {
    throw new SchemaValidationException(ErrorMessage.SCHEMA_VALIDATION_FAILED, {
        issues: result.issues,
    });
}

return result.data;
```

## Transactions

- Use MongoDB sessions for multi-document writes that must be atomic.
- The MongoDB replica set (`rs0`) is required. The Docker Compose stack provisions this automatically.
- Session lifecycle: `startSession()` → `startTransaction()` → `commitTransaction()` → `endSession()`.
- Always call `endSession()` in a `finally` block.
- Call `abortTransaction()` only when the transaction has NOT yet been committed (`isCommitted` guard).
- See `backend/backend.mdc` for the canonical transaction code pattern.

## Unique Constraints

- The `users` collection has a unique index on `email`.
- MongoDB code `11000` (duplicate key) is handled automatically by `exceptionsMiddleware` → `ConflictException`.
- DO NOT manually catch `11000` in controllers or repositories.

## Infrastructure

- MongoDB version: `mongo:7` with replica set `rs0` (required for transactions).
- Connection is managed by `aop/db`. DO NOT create additional `MongoClient` instances.
- Integration tests connect to a separate MongoDB instance configured via `.env.integration.test`.

## No Migration Tooling

- The project uses MongoDB (schema-less). There is no migration runner.
- Schema changes: update the Zod document schema + repository logic.
- For data backfills: write a one-off script in `backend/scripts/` and run via `ts-node`.
- DO NOT add destructive operations (drop, rename collection) without a documented migration plan.

# Anti-Patterns

- DO NOT return raw MongoDB documents without `parseSchema` validation.
- DO NOT call `db.collection()` outside a repository class.
- DO NOT create additional `MongoClient` connections outside `aop/db`.
- DO NOT run transactions on a standalone MongoDB instance (requires replica set).
- DO NOT manually catch duplicate key errors (11000) in controllers.

# Checklist

- [ ] All DB reads validated with `parseSchema` before use
- [ ] New repository methods follow `UserRepository` / `JobsRepository` pattern
- [ ] Transaction sessions closed in `finally` block
- [ ] No direct `db.collection()` calls outside repositories
